      "name": "Terrifying Touch",
      "sort": 800000,
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>A creature damaged by Aerilaya's touch that isn't already @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened} must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:33] save (@Check[type:will|dc:38] if the attack was a critical hit). If the creature fails its save, it's @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 2}; on a critical failure, the creature also cowers with fear and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.dfCMdR4wnpbYNTix]{Stunned 4}. If the creature is protected against fear by a spell or magic item, the banshee's touch first attempts to counteract the protection effect, with the effect of a 7th-level <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.9HpwDN4MYQJnW0LG]{Dispel Magic</em> spell.</p>"
        },
